node.text: @shiv421kobra but the original twin cinema by Yeow Kai Chai is a bit odd too. It was not really meant to be grammatical across 2 columns. Each individual line of a column is supposed to contain imagery that could correlate or contrast to the opposing line of the other column. So its supposed to be read according to the column it is in.

@sufy_wufy Some can be read across but it doesnt always work that way grammatically. It is best to read it as two discrete columns of poetry and try to see if it can work across too. But most of the time the two columns show correlating or contrasting images, or viewpoints at odds with each other, so they don't always work as a sentence across.
A twin cinema poem by Mark Rozzells
Qué the memes
Beautifully written

@markiemice You think us using cheap labour has no bearing on our progress? Then, why not send them all back if we don't need them?  Exploitation occurs in every business, food involves exploitation of animals and farmers, Amazon puts its warehouse employees under alot of stress and construction in highly developed areas uses migrant workers... Do you think the world is a utopia for your ideals? This is the real world bud.

@haz_ome who says we don't need them? We can need them and still pay them a fair wage and proper living quarters and still have progression. The issue is that the people at the top take too much of a cut, and they want to protect their profits more than provide welfare for their workers. Just because other people exploit their workers doesn't make it right.

@markiemice I told you from the start that I don't think it's right. All I'm saying is this is a part of the game. Exploitation happens and will continue happening. Nothing short of a concerted expensive effort will change it which I don't see happening. We still have a lot of archaic laws that should not exist in society.
